intro: Aerides quinquevulnera var. densiflora, commonly known as the dense-flowered orchid, is a species native to Southeast Asia. It is characterized by its compact growth habit and dense clusters of small, fragrant flowers. The plant typically produces white to pale yellow blooms that are highly ornamental. It thrives in humid, shaded environments and requires well-draining soil. This variety is popular among orchid enthusiasts for its beauty and relatively easy care requirements.
